The [`Image` constructor](https://openjfx.io/javadoc/19/javafx.graphics/javafx/scene/image/Image.html#%3Cinit%3E(java.lang.String)) expects a string representation of a URL. To get a URL for a `File`, use `selectedFile.toURI().toURL()`. To convert to a string representation in a robust way, call `toExternalForm()` on the `URL`. So you need

    Image img = new Image(selectedFile.toURI().toURL().toExternalForm());

(You can almost certainly rely on `selectedFile.toURI().toString()`; the code above just feels marginally more robust.)

